0outcomes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20partly%20due%20to%20decreased%20financial%20stress.%20More%20than%20three-quarters%20of%20moms%20said%20they%20worried%20less%20about%20sufficiently%20feeding%20their%20family%2C%20and%20were%20able%20to%20buy%20more%20nutritious%20food%20items.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParticipants%20were%20also%20more%20equipped%20to%20purchase%20things%20their%20kids%20wanted%20but%20weren't%20essential.%20About%2070%25%20of%20participants%20spent%20more%20time%20with%20their%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20participants%20didn't%20lose%20access%20to%20government%20benefits%2C%20though%20the%20increased%20income%20may%20have%20contributed%20to%20some%20families%20losing%20specific%20benefits%20like%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Elike%20CalFresh%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20state-level%20food%20assistance%20program%20that%20helps%20low-income%20residents%20purchase%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c499e224-915e-45ee-8420-9a8ceb589d71%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20basic%20income%20programs%20are%20aimed%20at%20parents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMarin%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECounty's%20pilot%20isn't%20the%20only%20basic%20program%20to%20focus%20on%20low-income%20mothers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20costs%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-young-children-financial-security-childcare-costs-data-2024-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBusiness%2520Insider%2520estimated%2520that%2520it%2Cchildcare%2520system%2520among%2520developed%2520countries.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20of%20%2426%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20raise%20one%20child%20in%20America.%20And%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funitedwaynca.org%2Fblog%2Fchild-poverty-in-america%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20United%20Way%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20infants%20and%20children%20living%20in%20poverty%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20experience%20homelessness%2C%20food%20insecurity%2C%20and%20low-educational%20attainment%20later%20in%