80%99.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fweb-series%2Fnews%2Fenglish%2Fthe-boys-season-4-episode-4-release-date-time-and-what-to-expect%2Farticleshow%2F111164350.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Josef%20Mengele%2C%20The%20Infamous%20Doctor%20At%20Nazi%20Concentration%20Camps%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EJosef%20Mengele%2C%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BAngel%20of%20Death%26quot%3B%2C%20is%20a%20haunting%20figure%20remembered%20for%20his%20atrocities%20at%20Auschwitz%20concentration%20camp%20during%20World%20War%20II.%20He%20gained%20the%20name%20for%20performing%20deadly%20experiments%20on%20prisoners%20at%20the%20Nazi%20concentration%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20on%20March%2016%2C%201911%2C%20in%20Gunzburg%2C%20Germany%2C%20he%20studied%20medicine%20and%20anthropology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Munich%20and%20received%20his%20doctorate%20in%201935.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMengele%20joined%20the%20Nazi%20Party%20in%201937%20and%20the%20Schutzstaffel%2C%20a%20major%20paramilitary%20organisation%20under%20Adolf%20Hitler%2C%20in%201938.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20arrived%20at%20Auschwitz%20in%20May%201943%20and%20was%20given%20the%20role%20of%20a%20camp%20physician.%20His%20main%20job%20was%20to%20decide%20the%20fate%20of%20prisoners%20as%20they%20arrived.%20He%20would%20choose%20who%20was%20to%20work%20under%20harsh%20conditions%20and%20who%20would%20go%20straight%20to%20the%20gas%20chambers%20to%20be%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20medical%20experiments%20were%20infamous%20for%20their%20extreme%20cruelty%20and%20lack%20of%20scientific%20value.%20He%20specifically%20focused%20on%20twins%2C%20believing%20that%20studying%20them%20could%20reveal%20genetic%20information%20useful%20to%20Nazi%20beliefs.%20Victims%2C%20including%20children%20and%20adults%2C%20endured%20surgeries%2C%20injections%20and%20other%20painful%20procedures%20without%20any%20form%20of%20pain%20relief%2C%20often%20leading%20to%20excruciating%20deaths.%20He%20even%20attempted%20to%20change%20eye%20colour%20through%20injections.%20These%20experiments%20were%20conducted%20without%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20victims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20grotesque%20perversion%20of%20the%20physician's%20role%2C%20Auschwitz's%20so%20called%20Angel%20of%20Death%20employed%20his%20knowledge%20of%20the%20workings%20of%20life%20in%20order%20to%20destroy%20it.%20He%20determined%20who%20would%20die%20immediately%20in%20the%20gas%20chambers%20of%20Auschwitz%20and%20who%20would%20be%20exploited%20for%20labor%20or%20'Nazi%20%26quot%3Bscience%20before%20being%20killed%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20US%20justice%20department%20said%20in%20a%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20prisoners%20arrived%20at%20Auschwitz%2C%20Mengele%20and%20his%20'doctor'%20colleagues%20selected%20for%20slave%20labor%20those%20who%20appeared%20medically%20fit%20(thus%20consigning%20them%20to%20toil%20under%20inhumane%20and%20often%20deadly%20conditions)%20or%20who%20could%20be%20used%20by%20the%20Third%20Reich%20in%20some%20other%20way.%20All%20other%20prisoners%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%2C%20were%20immediately%20murdered%20by%20gassing%20in%20specially%20designed%20asphyxiation%20chambers%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20experiments%2C%20he%20would%20allegedly%20remove%20the%20organs%20of%20prisoners%20without%20anaesthesia%20and%20intentionally%20infected%20his%20subjects%20with%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20his%20highly%20visible%20and%20significant%20role%20in%20the%20Hitler%20regime's%20homicidal%20reign%20of%20terror%2C%20Mengele%20effectively%20became%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20Holocaust%3B%20in%20particular%2C%20his%20name%20became%20synonymous%20with%20the%20evil%20of%20Auschwitz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20World%20War%20II%20came%20to%20an%20end%2C%20Mengele%20left%20Auschwitz%20and%20avoided%20being%20caught%20for%20many%20years.%20Despite%20efforts%20by%20those%20searching%20for%20Nazi%20criminals%20and%20international%20authorities%2C%20he%20managed%20to%20evade%20prosecution%20using%20different%20aliases%20in%20several%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201979%2C%20there%20was%20enough%20evidence%20to%20confirm%20Mengele's%20death%20in%20Brazil%2C%20where%20he%20had%20been%20living%20under%20a%20false%20name.%20Forensic%20investigations%20in%201985%20conclusively%20identified%20his%20remains%2C%20confirming%20he%20had%20drowned%20in%20a%20swimming%20accident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMengele%20became%20known%20as%20the%20embodiment%20of%20evil%20at%20Auschwitz%2C%20where%20over%20a%20million%20people%2C%20mostly%20Jews%2C%20were%20killed.%20His%20actions%2C%20seen%20as%20a%20horrific%20misuse%20of%20medical%20knowledge%2C%20showed%20how%20low%20people%20can%20stoop%20under%20oppressive%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1718961240000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Ftv5rhaa8_josef-mengele_625x300_21_June_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-was-angel-of-death-josef-the-doctor-of-auschwitz-during-world-war-ii-5937725%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Josef%20Mengele%2C%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BAngel%20of%20Death%26quot%3B%2C%20is%20a%20haunting%20figure%20remembered%20for%20his%20atrocities%20at%20Auschwitz%20concentration%20camp%20during%20World%20War%20II.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-was-angel-of-death-josef-the-doctor-of-auschwitz-during-world-war-ii-5937725%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-was-angel-of-death-josef-the-doctor-of-auschwitz-during-world-war-ii-5937725%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fwho-was-angel-of-death-josef-the-doctor-of-auschwitz-during-world-war-ii-5937725