world%2Feurope%2Fputins-hybrid-war-opens-a-second-front-on-natos-eastern-border%2Farticleshow%2F111160365.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fputins-hybrid-war-opens-a-second-front-on-natos-eastern-border%2Famp_articleshow%2F111160365.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fputins-hybrid-war-opens-a-second-front-on-natos-eastern-border%2Famp_articleshow%2F111160365.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWhy%20Haven't%20You%20Resigned%3F%26quot%3B%20Boeing%20Chief's%20Grilling%20By%20Senate%20Is%20Viral%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBoeing%20Co.%20Chief%20Executive%20Officer%20Dave%20Calhoun%20faced%20searing%20criticism%20in%20a%20Senate%20hearing%20that%20zeroed%20in%20on%20the%20company's%20manufacturing%20shortcomings%20and%20accused%20its%20leader%20of%20putting%20profit%20ahead%20of%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalhoun's%20testimony%20before%20a%20subcommittee%20chaired%20by%20Senator%20Richard%20Blumenthal%20of%20Connecticut%20marked%20his%20first%20public%20appearance%20before%20Congress%20since%20taking%20over%20the%20top%20job%20at%20Boeing%20in%20early%202020.%20After%20Boeing's%20safety%20record%20came%20under%20renewed%20public%20scrutiny%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20a%20near-catastrophic%20accident%20in%20January%2C%20the%20CEO%20was%20called%20to%20appear%20in%20Washington%20to%20defend%20his%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20and%20your%20board%20of%20directors%20have%20a%20duty%20to%20your%20shareholders%2C%20but%20they%20will%20be%20deeply%20ill%20served%20if%20you%20fail%20to%20correct%20course%20and%20confront%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20this%20broken%20safety%20culture%2C%26quot%3B%20Blumenthal%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20Connecticut%2C%20said%20in%20his%20opening%20comments.%20%26quot%3BFor%20Boeing%2C%20it%20is%20a%20moment%20of%20reckoning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalhoun%20began%20with%20a%20gesture%20of%20contrition%20by%20apologizing%20directly%20to%20relatives%20of%20people%20who%20died%20in%20two%20crashes%20involving%20Boeing%20aircraft%20in%202018%20and%202019.%20The%20hearing%20was%20at%20times%20testy%2C%20with%20Blumenthal%20accusing%20Boeing%20of%20providing%20what%20he%20called%20%26quot%3Bgobbledygook%26quot%3B%20documents%20to%20the%20panel%2C%20while%20others%20took%20offense%20at%20Calhoun's%20compensation%20or%20his%20perceived%20lack%20of%20engagement%20with%20whistleblowers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20here%20in%20the%20spirit%20of%20transparency%20and%20I'm%20here%20to%20take%20responsibility%2C%26quot%3B%20Calhoun%20told%20reporters%20ahead%20of%20the%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20almost%20two-hour%20hearing%20exposed%20the%20challenge%20of%20turning%20around%20a%20US%20manufacturing%20icon%20that%20senators%20said%20had%20lost%20its%20way.%20Calhoun%20sought%20to%20defend%20his%20record%2C%20saying%20he'd%20done%20everything%20he%20believed%20was%20required%20and%20calling%20some%20of%20the%20changes%20on%20his%20watch%20%26quot%3Bdramatic.%26quot%3B%20Blumenthal%20retorted%20that%20Boeing%20had%20done%20%26quot%3Bvirtually%20nothing%26quot%3B%20and%20instead%20only%20recycled%20%26quot%3Bold%20ideas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlumenthal%20asked%20the%20CEO%20to%20explain%20how%20Boeing%20allegedly%20retaliated%20against%20whistleblowers%20while%20at%20the%20same%20time%20encouraging%20workers%20to%20come%20forward%20with%20complaints.%20When%20asked%20if%20anyone%20had%20been%20fired%20for%20punishing%20whistleblowers%2C%20Calhoun%20said%20the%20company%20had%20done%20so%20but%20could%20not%20specify%20how%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalhoun%20said%20he'd%20not%20spoken%20to%20any%20whistleblowers%20directly.%20He%20acknowledged%20that%20doing%20so%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20idea.%26quot%3B%20More%20than%20a%20dozen%20have%20contacted%20the%20committee%20to%20share%20their%20concerns%2C%20Blumenthal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20CEO%2C%20Calhoun%20has%20presided%20over%20one%20of%20the%20most%20turbulent%20stretches%20in%20Boeing's%20century-long%20history.%20The%20planemaker%20has%20wracked%20up%20almost%20%2426%20billion%20in%20annual%20losses%20during%20his%20watch%20as%20it%20dealt%20with%20a%20global%20grounding%20of%20the%20737%20Max%2C%20the%20pandemic%2C%20worker%20exodus%20and%20supply%20chain%20chaos.%20In%20January%2C%20a%20Boeing%20aircraft%20suffered%20a%20near-catastrophic%20accident%20while%20in%20flight%2C%20prompting%20the%20latest%20crisis%20at%20the%20manufacturer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Calhoun%20stressed%20transparency%20and%20vowed%20to%20uphold%20accountability%20by%20senior%20management%2C%20the%20pressure%20to%20speed%20up%20manufacturing%20and%20deliveries%20often%20took%20precedence%20on%20the%20factory%20floor%2C%20whistleblowers%20have%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quality%20lapses%20at%20Boeing%20and%20supplier%20Spirit%20AeroSystem%20Holdings%20Inc.%2C%20which%20makes%20the%20737%20Max's%20hull%2C%20came%20to%20the%20forefront%20after%20the%20jet's%20suffered%20an%20airborne%20blowout%20of%20a%20fuselage%20panel%20in%20January.%20While%20no%20one%20on%20board%20was%20killed%2C%20investigators%20determined%20that%20the%20nearly%20new%20jet%20was%20delivered%20without%20four%20bolts%20needed%20to%20secure%20the%20door%20plug.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20harshest%20criticism%20was%20leveled%20at%20Calhoun's%20compensation%20package%20for%202023%20totaling%20almost%20%2433%20million%2C%20with%20Missouri%20Republican%20Josh%20Hawley%20saying%20it%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Btravesty%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20CEO%20was%20still%20in%20his%20job%2C%20asking%20if%20he%20would%20resign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSenator%2C%20I'm%20sticking%20this%20through%2C%26quot%3B%20Calhoun%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%